content:
Insurance UI templates work with OmniScripts to create an attractive end-user experience that integrates data such as rated products, insured items, available coverages, calculated prices, and coverage attributes.

UI templates contain the following:

CSS
Javascript
HTML

Installing Insurance UI Templates

OmniScript templates control the look, feel, and some of the behavior of insurance and health insurance OmniScripts.

To make Vlocity Insurance/Vlocity Health work, you must install the following OmniScript template datapacks:

Install BaseUITemplates
Install ObjectDocumentCreationUITemplates (if you have purchased Vlocity Contracts Lifecycle Management)
Install OmniScript Lightning
Install OmniScript Newport
Install VlocityInsOSTemplates

VlocityInsOS Templates

ins-coverages-os-template

Displays coverages for a specified insurance policy. Includes mandatory and optional coverages.

Calculates taxes, fees, total premium price, and changes that price on the fly, as the user makes changes to coverages.

Used for quote-rate-apply flows.

ins-os-coverage-component

Displays the coverages available for a rated policy.

Contains the ins-os-attribute-component template.

Used for quote-rate-apply flows.

Starting with version 8, this template is contained by the ins-coverages-os-template.

ins-os-attribute-component

Displays the attributes of coverages for a rated policy.

Used for quote-rate-apply flows.

Starting with version 8, this template is contained by the ins-os-coverage-component template, which is contained by the ins-coverages-os-template.

ins-os-multi-item

Displays coverages for a specified insurance policy that includes multiple insured items. When Custom plan details is clicked, shows mandatory and optional coverages.

Calculates total premium price, taxes and fees on the premium, and changes those prices on the fly, as the user makes changes to coverages.

Used for quote-rate-apply flows.

This template is available in Vlocity Insurance/Vlocity Health Summer '18 and later.

ins-os-multi-person

Displays coverages for a specified insurance policy that includes multiple insured people. When Custom plan details is clicked, shows mandatory and optional coverages.

Calculates total premium price, and changes that price on the fly, as the user makes changes to coverages.

Used for quote-rate-apply flows.

This template is available in Vlocity Insurance/Vlocity Health Summer '18 and later.

ins-os-census-upload

Lets a user upload a health insurance customer census in CSV file form.

Used for health enrollment flows.

ins-os-confirmation

Displays a confirmation when a user purchases a policy. Pulls the policy number, policy name, premium, effective date, expiration date, calculated taxes, calculated fees, and payment method.

Used at the end of quote-rate-bind, policy purchase, and renewal flows.

ins-os-enrollee-benefits-summary

Displays a summary of insurance policy products chosen by the enrollee. Includes details of each policy product.

User cannot change any values on this template.

Used in health enrollment flows.

ins-os-product-details-compare-modal

Health insurance template that displays available insurance products so a user can compare options.

User cannot change any values on this template.

Used in health enrollment flows.

ins-os-product-rules-review

Displays rules that have been triggered by a user's selections. Pulls the name of the rule and the reason the rule was triggered.

Users cannot interact with this template.

Used in quote-rate-apply flows.

ins-os-product-selection

Displays available products for selection, including default coverage limits, deductible, and premium.

Users can choose a product, but cannot change any values in this template.

Used in quote-rate-apply flows.

ins-os-quote-confirmation

Displays a confirmation when a user gets a quote. Pulls the quote number, quote name, the date the quote will expire, the calculated annual premium, the taxes and fees on the premium, and the total premium for the quoted policy.
title: Insurance UI Templates and Installation
